## Inspiration

Portions of this software were inspired by and derived from Mark LaCroix's and 
Noble Robot's Noble Engine. While there are some similarities in 
functionality, the implementation in Roxy is distinctly different, with 
substantial modifications and additions. Features such as scene lifecycle 
management, transitions, input handling, sprite management, sprite animations, 
the extended implementation of `playdate.ui.gridview`, game data management, 
and game settings management are heavily adapted and expanded from the 
concepts in Noble Engine. The implementation has been tailored to fit the 
specific needs and design patterns of Roxy, incorporating similar 
functionalities but with notable adaptations and enhancements, ensuring a 
unique approach. Roxy includes distinct implementations, unique additions, 
structural differences, and custom design patterns, making it a separate work. 
Additionally, Roxy features many non-derivative aspects, such as a distinct 
project organization, singleton managers, object pools, delta time, and 
performance enhancements in C. We aim to continue developing Roxy as a bespoke 
and customized game engine with an emphasis on performance and ease of use.

Noble Engine (https://github.com/NobleRobot/NobleEngine) is licensed under the 
MIT License:

